STEP 2: Security Group
To control network access, a AWS Security Groups configuration was applied to the EC2 instance. The security group was set up to allow inbound traffic on port 22 for SSH access, port 80 for HTTP, and port 5000 for the Flask application. This ensured that only required ports were open while maintaining basic security. The rules were configured to allow access from any IP address for testing purposes, enabling easy connectivity during development.    

