NETWORKING SETUP 

STEP 1:  Create VPC
 A virtual Private Cloud (VPC) was created to isolated the cloud infrastructure. The VPC uses the CIDR block 10.0.0.0/16 allowing scalable IP addressing.
STEP 2:  Subnets
  Two subnets were created in different availability zones to support high availability. 
STEP 3:    Internet  Gateway 
   Internet gateway was created and attached to enable internet access.
STEP 4:  Route Table
  A route table was configured with a default route 0.0.0.0/0 pointing to the internet gateway allowing inbound and outbound traffic. 
STEP:5 Load balancer
A target group was created to route incoming traffic to EC2 instances. Health checks were configured to monitor application availability.
An Application Load Balancer was configured to distribute incoming traffic across the EC2 instance. This improves application availability and ensures scalability by handling multiple requests efficiently.
STEP:6 Auto scaling group
An Amazon Machine Image (AMI) was created from the configured EC2 instance to serve as a template for launching multiple instances in the Auto Scaling group.
Auto Scaling can be implemented to automatically manage the number of EC2 instances based on application load. This ensures high availability, scalability, and cost efficiency in production environments. 
