 DATABASE 
 STEP 1: Create RDS Instance
 An Amazon RDS MySQL database instance was created to store application data. The database was configured using the free tier template with public access enabled for testing purposes.
 STEP 2: Configure Database Access
 The database security group was configured to allow inbound traffic on port 3306, enabling communication between the EC2 instance and the RDS database.
STEP 3: Connect EC2 to RDS
The EC2 instance was successfully connected to the RDS database using the MySQL client, verifying that the application server can communicate with the database layer.


MONITORING 
 Using cloud watch
Monitoring was implemented using Amazon CloudWatch to track system performance and application health. Key metrics such as CPU utilization, network traffic, and instance status were continuously monitored. CloudWatch alarms were configured to notify administrators when CPU usage exceeded predefined thresholds. Additionally, log monitoring was enabled to capture application and system-level events, ensuring proactive issue detection and resolution.


